{
  "texts": [
    "Instead of shooting videos in a lab, Sigurdsson et al.",
    "ensured diversity by distributing and crowdsourcing the entire video creation process, from scripting to video recording and annotation.",
    "Following this process, the authors collated a new dataset, i.e., Charades.",
    "Hundreds of people recorded videos and went about their daily leisure activities at home.",
    "The dataset consists of 9848 annotated videos, with an average length of 30 s, showing the activities of 267 people across three continents, with more than 15 percent featuring more than one person."
  ]
}